    {
      "cve": "CVE-2022-1373",
      "cwe": {
        "id": "CWE-23",
        "name": "Relative Path Traversal"
      },
      "notes": [
        {
          "category": "summary",
          "text": "The \u201crestore configuration\u201d feature of Softing Secure Integration Server is vulnerable to a directory traversal vulnerability when processing zip files. An attacker can craft a zip file to load an arbitrary dll and execute code. Using the \"restore configuration\" feature to upload a zip file containing a path traversal file may cause a file to be created and executed upon touching the disk.CVE-2022-1373 has been assigned to this vulnerability. A CVSS v3 base score of 7.2 has been calculated; the CVSS vector string is (AV:N/AC:L/PR:H/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H).",
